Thr Interim Management Committee of the league has said the 2023/24 Nigeria Professional Football League season will kickoff on the weekend of August 26-27. The abridged 2022/23 season ended earlier this month with Enyimba winning their ninth league title at the Super 6 playoffs in Lagos After the successful completion of the abridged season which was necessitated to bridge the gap of the Nigerian league calendar, the IMC also announced that clubs should begin the process of club licensing. In a related development, the NPFL transfer window will open on Saturday (today), July 1 and close on September 1, 2023.